<template><div><h1 id="is-absolute" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#is-absolute" aria-hidden="true">#</a> is-absolute <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/is-absolute" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://img.shields.io/npm/v/is-absolute.svg?style=flat" alt="NPM version"><ExternalLinkIcon/></a> <a href="https://npmjs.org/package/is-absolute" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://img.shields.io/npm/dm/is-absolute.svg?style=flat" alt="NPM monthly downloads"><ExternalLinkIcon/></a> <a href="https://npmjs.org/package/is-absolute" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://img.shields.io/npm/dt/is-absolute.svg?style=flat" alt="NPM total downloads"><ExternalLinkIcon/></a> <a href="https://travis-ci.org/jonschlinkert/is-absolute" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://img.shields.io/travis/jonschlinkert/is-absolute.svg?style=flat&amp;label=Travis" alt="Linux Build Status"><ExternalLinkIcon/></a></h1>
<blockquote>
<p>Returns true if a file path is absolute. Does not rely on the path module and can be used as a polyfill for node.js native <code v-pre>path.isAbolute</code>.</p>
</blockquote>
<h2 id="install" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#install" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Install</h2>
<p>Install with <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">npm<ExternalLinkIcon/></a>:</p>
<div class="language-bash ext-sh line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-bash"><code>$ <span class="token function">npm</span> <span class="token function">install</span> --save is-absolute
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers" aria-hidden="true"><div class="line-number"></div></div></div><p>Originally based on the <code v-pre>isAbsolute</code> utility method in <a href="https://github.com/visionmedia/express" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">express<ExternalLinkIcon/></a>.</p>
<h2 id="usage" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#usage" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Usage</h2>
<div class="language-javascript ext-js line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-javascript"><code><span class="token keyword">var</span> isAbsolute <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token function">require</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token string">'is-absolute'</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>

<span class="token function">isAbsolute</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token string">'a/b/c.js'</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token comment">//=> 'false'</span>
<span class="token function">isAbsolute</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token string">'/a/b/c.js'</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token comment">//=> 'true'</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers" aria-hidden="true"><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div></div></div><p><strong>Explicitly test windows paths</strong></p>
<div class="language-javascript ext-js line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-javascript"><code>isAbsolute<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">posix</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token string">'/foo/bar'</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
isAbsolute<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">posix</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token string">'/user/docs/Letter.txt'</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token comment">//=> true</span>

isAbsolute<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">posix</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token string">'foo/bar'</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token comment">//=> false</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers" aria-hidden="true"><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div></div></div><p><strong>Explicitly test windows paths</strong></p>
